CHAT.comment: Birthdate of ERI not indicated Eric didn't talk very much; he was generally silent when involved in any activity; did not spontaneously name objects as he had at eric02.cha. Much of his verbalization is jargon , as before , with less tendency to persevere. When he isn't understood , he tends to turn to something else. He was quite happy , laughed and participated well. His attention to activities and toys was variable; when self-motivated he persevered with an activity (such as pushing pegs into tinker toy wheel) for up to 15-20 minutes. Otherwise he would ignore an activity or toy , or attend only briefly. The most productive utterance was "more plus Noun" and "no plus more plus Noun" used appropriately. He named a piece of popcorn on the flooor as either "dirty" or "candy" but did not combine. His Mother reported that his vocabulary has increased in the last 6 weeks but she hasn't heard many two word constructions; "more xxx" and "no more xxx" are the most productive. He also says "baby cry" when he hears a baby crying. He is using some nouns in requesting (e.g. "juice" , "apple") but still resorts to a low pitched whine or grunt when he wants something done (such as fixing the slide) or when he wants something which he can't name.
